string.name: DetailPage_text
string.value:
All living things evolve freely. HarmonyOS is an operating system for multi-device experience, so providing users with a comfortable and convenient multi-device operating experience is the core point of HarmonyOS different from other operating systems.

On the one hand, interface design/component design needs to have a good adaptive ability to quickly develop different screen sizes.On the other hand, we want a multi-device experience that strikes a good balance between consistency and differentiation.

● Consistency: The design of elements in the interface and the way of interaction should be consistent as far as possible in order to reduce the learning cost of users.

● Difference: Different types of equipment in the screen size, interaction, use scenarios, user groups and other aspects will have a certain difference, in order to provide users with the right operating experience, we need to be differentiated for different types of equipment design.
